<SLUG> BC-MERRILL-SHAKEUP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MERRILL NAMES NEW CHIEF FOR GLOBAL DEBT 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By JOSEPH KAHN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The shake-up in the executive suite at Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
continued Friday as the brokerage firm announced that it had
replaced the head of its global debt business.
</P>
<P>
   Merrill named G. Kelly Martin, 39, as chief of the debt
business, replacing Seth Waugh, who will become Martin's deputy.
Waugh had been co-head of the 1,900-employee global debt unit since
1997.
</P>
<P>
   The change was the second in as many days at the firm. On
Thursday, Merrill named Richard Dunn to replace Daniel Napoli as
head of its risk management team. Both Waugh and Napoli were
demoted, but Merrill said it was not assigning blame to them and
that both would remain with the firm.
</P>
<P>
   ``We felt it was a good idea to bring in some new perspective to
our debt business,'' said Thomas Davis, Merrill's executive vice
president for the corporate and institutional client group.
</P>
<P>
   The demotions are part of a broader revamping at Merrill. On
Tuesday, the firm announced a third-quarter loss of $164 million
and said it would dismiss 3,400 workers.
</P>
<P>
   Waugh had shared responsibility for the debt unit with Conrad
Voldstad, who left the position last month when he was assigned to
a team overseeing Long-Term Capital Management, the hedge fund that
Merrill helped rescue.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-17-98 0027EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
