 TICKETS SOLD on SATURDAY FOR GAMES 5 AND 6  
(js) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ There are a good many people in New York, David Wells
of the Yankees most vocal among them, who do not believe that the
World Series will last more than five games. Nonetheless, tickets
will go on sale at 11 a.m. Sunday for Games 5 and 6.
</P>
<P>
   The tickets will be sold over the telephone through Ticketmaster
at (212) 307-1212 or (800) 669-0375. Credit cards are the only
payment accepted. The games would be played next Saturday and
Sunday nights. If the games are not necessary, refunds will be
made.
</P>
<P>
   Yankee officials were uncertain on Saturday exactly how many
tickets would be available, but only 5,000 per game were sold to
the general public for Games 1 and 2.
</P>
