tons of press about the violence just killed it. If it had been
less violent, it would have been a huge hit.''
</P>
<P>
   Still, any property can click if it hits at the right time,
which is why the wheels of commerce cranking out toys and
collectibles never stop turning. The potential is huge: Spending on
and by children tripled during the 1990s; children under 6 have
become a potent force for properties like the Teletubbies, Barney
and Winnie the Pooh; and the average 10-year-old's weekly allowance
rose from $7.90 a week in 1991 to $13.93 last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every four or five years, you have a whole new group of kids
come into the market,'' Scher noted. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
