<SLUG> BC-STARS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FILM STARS BACK RIVALS IN ARIZONA 6TH DISTRICT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By ALEXA HAUSSLER  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Picture the flicks: the ``Sundance Kid'' takes on ``Ben Hur''.
</P>
<P>
   Or ``The Natural'' goes to bat against, well, Moses.
</P>
<P>
   Sounds like pure Hollywood. But two legendary film stars have
made Arizona politics their latest projects.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Redford and Charlton Heston are taking sides in Arizona's
closest, and most dramatic, race: The 6th Congressional District
bout of incumbent Republican J.D. Hayworth and Democrat Steve
Owens.
</P>
<P>
   This time, instead of launching home runs or bringing down a
president, Robert Redford is flexing his Hollywood muscle for
Owens, who came within 2,500 votes of defeating Hayworth in 1996 in
one of the state's ugliest election battles.
</P>
<P>
   Redford praises Owens in a radio ad, which started airing
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ``As Arizona experiences some of the fastest growth in the
country, Steve Owens wants to hold developers accountable and fight
to manage our growth and to protect the desert,'' the liberal
Redford says in the advertisement.
</P>
<P>
   Owens said in a press release Friday that Redford offered to do
the radio spot because the League of Conservation Voters, a group
in which Redford is active, endorsed him.
</P>
<P>
   Hayworth spokesman Jeff Breedlove said Saturday the congressman
isn't sweating Redford's endorsement of his opponent.
</P>
<P>
   ``In fact, it appears that Mr. Redford is auditioning for a new
role here. Perhaps a remake of the ``Terminator'' because he's
trying to destroy the rural economy which is so important to the
6th District of Arizona,'' Breedlove said.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, rather than parting the Red Sea or painting the
Sistine Chapel, National Rifle Association President Heston is
putting in a good word for Hayworth.
</P>
<P>
   Heston, who is wildly popular with the state's senior citizens,
agreed to make a personal appearance in the district and to do a
radio ad for Hayworth, Breedlove said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe Mr. Heston's supporting Congressman Hayworth because
he recognizes that Congressman Hayworth has done a great job
listening to the people of Arizona and representing the mainstream
common sense values of Arizona,'' Breedlove said. &QL; 
 &UR; Alexa Haussler can be reached at 444-7481 or at
alexa.haussler &LR; pni.com via
 &UR; e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
