<HEADLINE>
ROENICK LOSES WISDOM TEETH 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SCOTTSDALE, ARIZ.- Spectators at Saturday's Phoenix Coyotes
practice were surprised to see rookie  &UR; Daniel Briere skating at
center with the No. 1 line instead of  &UR; Jeremy Roenick.
</P>
<P>
   While the move definitely shows Briere is ready to return to
action after the concussion he suffered in the final preseason game
against Anaheim, it was not a significant move.
</P>
<P>
   Roenick was absent from practice after having four wisdom teeth
pulled on Friday. Defenseman  &UR; Keith Carney also sat out the workout
because of back spasms but is expected to be ready for Monday
night's game against Boston.
</P>
<P>
   While Briere's presence with the No. 1 line might not be
permanent, he did leave a dandy drop pass that  &UR; Keith Tkachuk
quickly one-timed for a goal.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEW NUMBER: How hard was Briere hit by Anaheim's  &UR; Ruslan
 &UR; Salei? &UR; Hard enough to knock 46 numbers off his game sweater. The
rookie has scrapped the No. 54 and will wear No. 8.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was the first number I had when I started playing hockey,''
Briere said. ``And I wore it in juniors for awhile, too. I'm glad,
but I was happy with No. 54 as long I as I got to stay in the
NHL.''
</P>
<P>
   Briere said  &UR; Jim Johnson, &UR; who wore the digit last season before
retiring and joining the team's radio broadcast as an analyst, has
given him some friendly grief about taking the number.
</P>
<P>
   What, Johnson thought the Coyotes would retire it? &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
